---
source: crates/plasm-agent-core/src/mcp_server.rs
expression: "super::mcp_server_initialize_instructions()"
---
Plasm is **several MCP tools**; use what you need, in order. **`plasm_context`** opens one logical session; **`plasm`** returns a **dry-run plan** for programs inside it; **`plasm_run`** performs **live execution** after you review that plan; **`discover_capabilities`** finds **`api`** and **`entity`** values that match your intent when you do not already know them. **Skip `discover_capabilities`** when you already know every **`api`/`entity`** pair you need.
     **One user goal ŌåÆ one stable **`intent`** ŌåÆ one **`plasm_context`**.** `logical_session_ref` slots (`s0`, `s1`, ŌĆ”) are **per logical goal**, not per API. Federated example: `[{"api":"pokeapi","entity":"Pokemon"},{"api":"linear","entity":"Issue"}]` in **one** **`seeds`** array ŌĆö not a second context open for the same task.
     **`discover_capabilities`**: **one call per user goal** with one **`intent`** string for the whole task (multi-API goals in that sentence). No keyword arrays, **`query`**/**`utterance`**, or per-integration splits. Reply is a fenced table (**`api`**, **`entity`**, **`description`**); merge rows into one **`plasm_context`** **`seeds`**. Retry only if entities are missing. Use **`typed: true`** when ambiguous.
     **`plasm_context`**: see the **`plasm_context`** tool description for seeds shape, teaching TSV output, and `_meta.plasm` continuity. **Steady state:** reuse **`logical_session_ref`** with **`plasm`** / **`plasm_run`** ŌĆö do **not** repeat **`plasm_context`** with identical **`seeds`** every turn.
     **`plasm`**: pass **`logical_session_ref`** and one **`program`** string.
**JSON `program` string:** Use literal newline characters (U+000A) between statements when you have more than one bindingŌĆötypically one `ident = ŌĆ”` per line, then bare comma-separated roots on the last line(s). Spaces do not separate statements. (Wire JSON may show `\n`; the parsed string must still contain real newlines.)

**Heredoc:** After `<<TAG` on the opener line, start the body on the next line; close with a line whose trimmed text is `TAG` (or `TAG)` / `TAG,` / `TAG}`). First trimmed-line match closes the heredocŌĆöuse a long opaque `TAG` for unconstrained payloads (MIME, markdown, logs).

Executable grammar (`e#` / `m#` / `p#`), bracket-render, and `.content` rules: **`plasm_context` teaching TSV** plus the **`plasm`** tool description ŌĆö not repeated here.
     **`plasm`** is **plan-only** (no live HTTP). Prefer **one** `program` per call (bindings on separate lines; comma-separated roots on the final line for multi-return). Multi-root answers: review with **`plasm`**, execute with **`plasm_run`**. Never prefix roots with `return`.
     **`plasm_run`**: same arguments as **`plasm`**. Call **only after** the **`plasm`** dry-run plan matches intentŌĆöthis tool performs **live** HTTP/API execution (and may return run snapshot URIs).
     **Paging:** follow **`page(s0_pgN)`** / `_meta.plasm.paging` in the same logical session for more rows.
     **Run snapshots:** `plasm://ŌĆ”` URIs are MCP **`resources/read`** targets, not Plasm expressions ŌĆö call **`resources/read`** for full JSON when the summary points there.
